God Wars Dungeon.name: God Wars Dungeon
npcs: Ashuelot Reis|quote=Once Nex was no longer an immediate threat
they built the Temple of Lost Ancients around her. Most of the temple has since fallen to ruin
but you can still see some of the remains.}} is a [[dungeons|dungeon]] where armies of various [[gods]] fight
left over from the [[God Wars]].

Kandarin.name: Kandarin
npcs: Lord Baxtorian Cadarn|loc=Song of the Elves|quote=While we were gone
an uprising had occurred in the eastern kingdom. We took our best fighters to Prifddinas
those that remained were unable to hold back the enemy.}} In the end
Baxtorian did not successfully quash Iorwerth's insurrection and was forced to turn back to their territory east through the [[Underground Pass (dungeon)|Underground Pass]] with his forces
only to find the previously prosperous kingdom in ruin. On learning that his wife had been taken
her location and retrieval became an immediate priority there
alongside getting his people to safety.{{citeNPC|npc=Islwyn|loc=Song of the Elves|quote=While he was fighting Lord Iorwerth
invaders took control of our kingdom to the east. They kidnapped Glarial
Baxtorian's wife.}}{{citeNPC|npc=Lord Baxtorian Cadarn|loc=Song of the Elves|quote=My Glarial... She mattered more to me than anything else
but she was lost to me. The enemy took her

so I searched far and wide to find her again.[...]My wife was taken and most of my people were slaughtered. I turned my attention to finding my wife and getting the rest of my people to safety.}} However
he failed to find her
and having been exhausted from the conflicts in both of his homes and a hapless pursuit to find his lover
he pinned his hopes on the sliver of chance she would live through this tragedy and sealed himself in the Baxtorian Falls
where she would come to awaken him.{{citeNPC|npc=Lord Baxtorian Cadarn|loc=Song of the Elves|quote=At times I came close
but in the end
I was too weak to carry on. I knew there was a chance she may live though
so I sealed myself away
hoping she would be the one to wake me.}} Unfortunately

Glarial's body had later been recovered and her remains placed in an urn laid to rest in the [[Glarial's tomb|tomb]] dedicated to her near Baxtorian Falls.{{citeNPC|npc=Hadley|loc=Waterfall Quest|quote=Glarial was kidnapped while Baxtorian was away
but they eventually recovered her body and brought her home to rest.}}

Temple of the Eye (location).name: Temple of the Eye (location)
npcs: Viggora|quote=It was then [after the Betrayal of Zaros] that the other gods appeared and banished Zamorak from the world completely for daring to kill one of their kind
although as it turned out it didn't quite work out that way for them
when he returned stronger than ever
a god himself.}} During this time
possession of the Stone went to [[Saradomin]]
who then hid it beneath the waves somewhere south of [[Hallowvale]]. [[Aliya]] and [[Zachariah]]
[[Justiciar]]s of the Lion and Owl
were tasked with protecting the artefact;{{CiteNPC|npc=Zachariah|quote=...he [Saradomon] has given us the task of protecting it [the Eye].}} Aliya was tasked to build the temple to house the artefact
{{CiteNPC|npc=Zachariah|quote=You must build a sanctuary for the Eye. The forces of chaos already seek to reobtain it
as do countless others.}} known to them as "The Eye"
while Zachariah was to hunt down and slay those who would try to claim it
including [[Porazdir]]
one of Zamorak's generals.{{CiteNPC|npc=Zachariah|quote=Zamorak has tasked his collector with finding the Eye. I will hunt him down before he does
along with any others who would try to claim it.}}

Civitas illa Fortis.name: Civitas illa Fortis
npcs: Curator Herminius|quote=For example
here in Fortis
you'll find yourself surrounded by Perican archetecture
whereas over in the Tlati Rainforest
the influence of the Talkasti remains clear.}} featuring several notable landmarks such as the [[Fortis Colosseum]]
[[Sunrise Palace]]
and the [[Grand Museum]].

Underground Military Glider Hangar.name: Underground Military Glider Hangar
npcs: Daero|loc=Monkey Madness I|quote=We try to ensure the location of the hangar remains a secret. If you must know something
then know that it lies directly beneath the Gnomeball pitch. However
I cannot reveal the location of its entrance.}} commissioned by [[Glough]]. It is full of military gnome gliders that are lighter and stronger than ordinary ones

intended by Glough to wage war against the humans by air should his land and sea attacks fail. He also installed a security measure requiring the facility to be 'reinitialised' periodically to maintain power supply.{{CiteNPC|npc=Daero|loc=Monkey Madness I|quote=Glough left a code on the facility
which periodically needs to be entered if we wish to maintain the supply of power. Without going through the process of reinitialisation
we cannot power the mechanism which deploys the military gliders.}}

Citharede Abbey.name: Citharede Abbey
npcs: Sister Scarophia|quote=I'd heard rumours that there was an Abbey up here somewhere
which sounded marvellous
but I seem to be in the wrong place.}} However
with the actual introduction of the Abbey
she was moved to a chapel within the Ferox Enclave
and her dialogue was adjusted to no longer reference the Abbey.

Gorak Plane.name: Gorak Plane
npcs: Duradel|quote=Be extremely careful
their [Gorak] touch drains health as well as skills!}}{{CiteNPC|npc=Fairy Nuff|quote=Goraks drain the life from their prey
so by using one of their claws we are hoping to draw the Queen's life essence back.}} as well as the world they live on. In doing so
they have effectively trapped themselves on this small plane
{{CiteNPC|npc=Fairy Nuff|quote=The fairy rings can take you to the plane that the Goraks are imprisoned on. Be careful
they are extremely dangerous creatures.}}{{CiteNPC|npc=Duradel|quote=Goraks are extremely aggressive creatures. They have been imprisoned on an alternative plane
which is only accesible by using the fairyrings.}} leaving what's left of it noticeably warped.

Karamja.name: Karamja
npcs: Kangai Mau|quote=[Player: Who are the Rantuki tribe?] A proud and noble tribe of Karamja. But now we are few
as men come from across sea
steal our land
and settle on our hunting grounds.}} Looting by the colonial factions is still not an uncommon occurrence
as evinced
for example
by the archaeologist [[Asgarnia Smith]] boasting about stealing the [[Golden Monkey of Tee-Tah-Toh]] from a "spooky old temple" he happened upon one day in the middle of the Karamjan jungle
under the auspices of the Archaeological Society of Varrock.{{CiteNPC|npc=Asgarnia Smith|quote=Well
this one time I found this spooky old temple in the middle of the jungle.}} Another notable case is the ancient temple laden with traps discovered by [[Cap'n Izzy No-Beard]]

who then decided to turn it into a [[Brimhaven Agility Arena|sports centre]].{{CiteNPC|npc=Cap'n Izzy No-Beard|quote=I'd found a huge cave with all these platforms. I reckon it be an ancient civilization that made it. I had to be mighty careful as there was these traps everywhere! Dangerous it was!}}

Fremennik Isles.name: Fremennik Isles
npcs: Mord Gunnars|quote=Jatizso ventured far into uncharted oceans

[...]}} until they were settled by the two youngest sons of a Fremennik king who ruled four generations before the present:{{CiteNPC|npc=Mord Gunnars|quote=Four generations ago there was a mighty king who ruled wisely and was loved by all. He had many sons
[...]. His youngest two sons
however
were a problem.}} Jatizso and Neitiznot.{{CiteNPC|npc=Maria Gunnars|quote=Their names were Jatizso and Neitiznot.}} As punishment for their squabbling
the king banished them from the realm until they had conquered lands of their own.{{CiteNPC|npc=Mord Gunnars|quote=As punishment for their squabbling he banished his sons from his realm
ordering that neither should return until they had conquered lands of their own.}} Jatizso came across a land rich in minerals
deep fjords and sweeping mountains.{{CiteNPC|npc=Mord Gunnars|quote=At last a promising land was sighted
a land rich in minerals
deep fjords and sweeping mountains.}} He then claimed the land
named it after himself

{{CiteNPC|npc=Mord Gunnars|quote=Jatizso claimed the land and named it after himself.}} built a citadel and set out to explore the kingdom.{{CiteNPC|npc=Mord Gunnars|quote=A mighty citadel was constructed to protect his land; then Jatizso set forth to explore his new kingdom.}}

Cam Torum.name: Cam Torum
npcs: Attala|quote=Before Lovakengj
there was Imcandoria. Our ancestors there were forced to abandon their home

just as we were forced to leave Kourend.}} descended from [[Lovakengj]] refugees who fled [[Xeric]]'s rule during the [[Age of Strife]].{{CiteNPC|npc=Curator Herminius|quote=Finally we have the dwarves. These were refugees from Lovakengj who established a home beneath Ralos' Rise
becoming known as the Dwarves of Cam Torum.}}{{CiteNPC|npc=Attala|quote=The Varlamorians won't mention this
but we were the first to settle here. Our ancestors saw the writing on the wall when Xeric came to power in Kourend. They chose not to stick around.}} Though part of [[Varlamore]] geographically
Cam Torum appears to be equivalent to an independent [[Kingdom|city-state]]
being governed by [[Highlord Katlo]] rather than [[Queen Zyanyi Arkan]]. Additionally
they do not appear to refer to themselves as of the Imcando

but rather as the "Dwarves of Cam Torum".{{CiteNPC|npc=Seer (The Darkfrost)|quote=...you should know that the Dwarves of Cam Torum take a different approach to worship than your kind.}}{{CiteNPC|npc=Blacksmith (Cam Torum)|quote=I am one of the Dwarves of Cam Torum
human!|loc=Perilous Moons}}{{CiteNPC|npc=Attala|quote=The Lovakengj dwarves have mostly forgotten their history.
but we Dwarves of Cam Torum remember it all too well.}}

Mort Myre Swamp.name: Mort Myre Swamp
npcs: Drezel|loc=Nature Spirit|quote=Mort Myre was once a beautiful forest by the name of Humblethorn until the evil denizens of Morytania descended.}} is a swampland in western [[Morytania]]. Typically players unlock the gate to the swampland by starting [[Nature Spirit]]
but they can also access it by [[Barrows teleport]] or [[Mort'ton teleport]] scrolls. It is plagued by [[ghast]]s

and not even a full inventory of [[food]] will keep players safe here because ghasts will decompose any kind of food. It is highly recommended for players to carry a [[Mort myre fungi|fungi]]-loaded [[druid pouch]]
which can only be obtained during Nature Spirit
with them as they travel through the swamp. Completing the quest is also a requirement to gain access to the gate shortcut.

Zanaris.name: Zanaris
npcs: Fairy Nuff|loc=Fairytale II - Cure a Queen|quote=The latest fairies to arrive have even reported that he has invited all sorts of monsters to the Lost City.}}

Waterbirth Island.name: Waterbirth Island
npcs: Jarvald|quote=It is a small crescent-shaped island just north-west of here
outerlander. We have many legends about it
such as the tale of the broken sky
and the day of the green seas.}} In recent times
the island had been free of the dagannoths that currently infest its caves
as Fremennik warriors had driven them back into the sea at an unspecified point in the past.{{CiteNPC|npc=Jarvald|quote=Aye
the dagger-mouths! The vile creatures lived near here once
but we had thought them all driven back to the ocean depths many moons past.}}

Rune essence mine.name: Rune essence mine
npcs: Mage of Zamorak|quote=A Zamorakian wizard made a great breakthrough in teleportation magic
but the Saradominists stole his research. They used it to perform a ritual
but their lack of understanding caused it to go wrong. The entire Wizards' Tower burnt down. Many were killed
and years of research was destroyed.}} They attempted a ritual using this breakthrough
but due to not understanding the magic
failed
and burned down the Wizards' Tower losing years of research. The Saradominist wizards blamed the Zamorakian wizards for the failure
and banished them from the Order
leading them to form the [[Zamorak Magical Institute]]. Eventually
the [[Player character|player]] assisted [[Archmage Sedridor]] in re-discovering the incantation used to teleport to the rune essence mine
and later on provided the Zamorakian mages with access to the mine in exchange for access to the [[Abyss]] for runecrafting.

Prifddinas.name: Prifddinas
npcs: Baxtorian|loc=Song of the Elves|quote=One of the security measures put in place during the God Wars
from the outside it seems like there's nothing there.}}

Kharyrll.name: Kharyrll
npcs: Golem (Desert Treasure II)|quote=Kharyrll was completely destroyed by Zamorakian forces.}} The modern-day town of [[Canifis]] now stands where the fortress once stood.

Kebos Lowlands.name: Kebos Lowlands
npcs: Tasakaal|quote=Our purpose was to wait. But we saw the world burn. We could not stand by and watch. So we left our people. Left our home. And took on a new purpose.}}. Once there
they renamed themselves the [[Tasakaal]] and created the [[Kahlith]]
their servants
to aid them in keeping life in check by maintaining "the balance": ''For every death
there must be a life. For every life
there must be a death.'' Despite this philosophy
they claim to not be servants of [[Guthix]]
whom they call a pretender.

The Teomat.name: The Teomat
npcs: Ennius Tullus|quote=The Teomat is the centre of all religion in Varlamore.}} The Teomat was built on Ralos' Rise due to it being a holy site
as it is said that the mountain was where [[Ralos]] made his first and only appearance.{{CiteNPC|npc=Nelta of Ralos|quote=The first and only time that Ralos appeared to us
he did so here on Ralos' Rise. The Teomat was built here as a result.}}

Arceuus Library.name: Arceuus Library
npcs: Chronicles of Xeric|loc=Library Historical Archive|quote=The Grand Library of Great Kourend has verified and collated the following extracts from various historical texts}} is a large library found in [[Arceuus]]. Created during the attack of the [[Wintertodt]] (known then as the Winter Beast) 1
360 years ago
its construction was [[Official Order of Construction|ordered]] by [[Lord Arceuus I]]
who requested all citizens submit writing
texts
documents and research from all cities in order to preserve the history of Great Kourend.

Northern Tundras.name: Northern Tundras
npcs: Undor|loc=The Forsaken Tower|quote=You're right with that one [laddie/lass]. Someone or something has made a small hole in the Doors.}} Although not much
it is enough for the Wintertodt imprisoned within to draw a small amount of power into the prison
creating trouble for the [[pyromancer]]s inside the prison.{{CiteNPC|npc=Undor|loc=The Forsaken Tower|quote=It's not much

but it's enough for that Wintertodt to be able to draw some power into the prison. Probably why them fiery lot have had so much trouble recently.}} Despite its repair by [[Undor]] using [[Dinh's hammer]] with the help of the player

it has already gained much power in the time the Doors were damaged and would take a longer time to be permanently subdued.{{CiteNPC|npc=Undor|loc=The Forsaken Tower|quote=[Player: Does this mean the Wintertodt won't be a threat anymore?] That should be the case in the long run. I suspect it will take a long time though. The Doors were damaged for a while and the Wintertodt will have gained a lot of power. I reckon that magic lot will have to do their fiery tricks for a bit longer before everything is back to normal.}}

Witchaven.name: Witchaven
npcs: Col. O'Niall|quote=When you introduce a large scale operation like the Fishing Platform

it takes away the business from the little guy. Almost overnight Witchaven became a ghost town.|loc=The Slug Menace}} It provides access to the [[Fishing Platform]] and features heavily in the [[Sea Slug]] and [[Slug Menace]] quests. It is also a notable [[fishing spot]].

Kalphite Cave.name: Kalphite Cave
npcs: Kalphite Queen head (mounted)|quote=Yes
you killed this queen
but by now another will have risen up! One kalphite may die but the hive goes on!}}

Annakarl.name: Annakarl
npcs: Golem (Desert Treasure II)|quote=Annakarl fell early in the war to forces of Saradomin. Attempts to reclaim the fortress have so far been unsuccessful.}} and likely destroyed during the [[God Wars]] by followers of [[Zamorak]] and [[Saradomin]]. [[Zilyana]]
a [[Icyene]] commander of the Saradominist forces
was likely injured during the battle in Annakarl

leading to the creation of [[Saradomin's tear]].{{CiteNPC|npc=Golem (Desert Treasure II)|quote=Last Known Location [of Zilyana]: Annakarl}}<ref>[[Saradomin's tear]]. ''Old School Runescape''. Examine text. "After a terrible battle
Saradomin wept over the wounds of his faithful Zilyana."</ref>

Sophanem.name: Sophanem
npcs: Sphinx|loc=Icthlarin's Little Helper|quote=Sophanem is called the city of the dead because the dead are brought here. Death plays a rather large role in the beliefs of the people and
as a result
the business.}}{{CiteNPC|npc=Wanderer|loc=Icthlarin's Little Helper|quote=It's the second city of the Menaphites
full of giant monuments to their dead.}} Unfortunately for the Sophanites
these treasure-filled tombs are a magnet for graverobbers such as [[Simon Templeton]]. It is the seat of the High Priest of Icthlarin
whose duties include the protection of the great pyramids and ensuring that the souls of the dead are protected from the [[Devourer]]

Icthlarin's deranged sister.{{CiteGeneral|url=https://wayback.archive-it.org/all/20090522043236/http://www.runescape.com/kbase/viewarticle.ws?article_id=2702|quote=As the leader of the Church of Icthlarin
and the guardian of the pyramids of Sophanem

it falls to the High Priest to ensure that the devourer - Icthlarin's godly foe - gains no foothold in the city.|name=hp|title=''RuneScape'' website - Game Guide - Area Guides - Cities and Towns - Sophanem}} [[Cat]]s and their protector
the [[Sphinx]]
play an important role in this latter task.{{CiteNPC|npc=Sphinx|loc=Icthlarin's Little Helper|quote=Cats play a significant role in the religion of this area
particularly when it comes to guarding the dead from The Devourer.}}

Ghorrock.name: Ghorrock
npcs: Hazeel|quote=Before the God Wars

a settlement of the old empire was found here.|loc=Secrets of the North|notes=as Big Fish (Hazeel)|name=}} Ghorrock is said to have once been part of larger settlement but on the surface only the fortress stood the test of time{{CiteNPC|npc=Hazeel|quote=The fortress to the east is all that remains on the surface

but there is much still hidden below.|loc=Secrets of the North|notes=as Big Fish (Hazeel)|name=}} including a mysterious [[Mahjarrat]] [[Old Shrine|ritual marker]]{{CiteNPC|npc=General Khazard|quote=We're blind here. My senses do nothing this close to the ritual marker.|loc=Secrets of the North|notes=as Dead Wolf (Khazard)|name=}} to the south. The surface area of the fortress is entirely inaccessible but below
following a cave-in during the events of [[Secrets of the North]] and further investigation in [[Desert Treasure II - The Fallen Empire|Desert Treasure II]]
an [[Ghorrock Dungeon|old dungeon]] and a [[Ghorrock Prison|great prison]]{{CiteNPC|npc=Hazeel|quote=A great prison
sealed long ago.|loc=Secrets of the North|notes=as Big Fish (Hazeel)|name=}} can be accessed.

Keldagrim.name: Keldagrim
npcs: Postie Pete|quote=Did you know that Keldagrim was originally constructed by a long lost clan who embraced the power of magic
and used it to aid with glorious buildings like the royal palace? They even stayed down there for 1000 years or more
in a time they call 'The age of Kings'.|name=postie}}{{CiteNPC |npc=Rind the gardener |loc=The Giant Dwarf |quote=We dwarves went underground a long time ago

see. For a while the city of Keldagrim was completely cut off from the rest of Gielinor simply waiting out the wars of the humans and the gods.}}{{NamedRef|hugi}} The history of Keldagrim is thereafter divided into at least three periods
most of which take place in the [[Fourth Age]]. They include the Era of Kings
the Rise of the Consortium
and the Era of Prosperity
as these eras are supposedly documented in the [[Keldagrim Library]].{{CiteNPC |npc=Librarian|loc=The Giant Dwarf|quote='''Librarian:''' You'll find books dating from many different eras as well
such as the Era of Kings
the Rise of the Consortium and the Era of Prosperity

our current era.
'''Player:''' How do these eras correspond with the Ages of the world?
'''Librarian:''' Oh
they are quite different

and most of them take place in the Fourth Age. Since dwarves hid underground for a long time to sit out the wars that rages above the ground our history books differ slightly from those written by humans|name=hugi}}

Myths' Guild.name: Myths' Guild
npcs: Erdan|quote=Quickly they [the Sect] established this guild with information preservation as their core goal
for men are recorders of history and magic is key for this to last.}} as well as distinguishing fact and myths throughout history
all of which are archived in the guild's Library of Knowledge.{{CiteNPC|npc=Alec Kincade|quote=As time passes
that which was once fact
becomes myth. Some tales are just that
tales. However
some tales are something more. Here at the Myths' Guild
we live to tell the difference between the two. If you wish to join us
you must do the same.}}

River Kelda.name: River Kelda
npcs: Miodvetnir|quote=We haul all our goods to the city by ship
you see.}}

Darkmeyer.name: Darkmeyer
npcs: Vanescula Drakan|loc=Sins of the Father|quote=Hallowvale was taken over by my kind
and Lowerniel became ruler of the newly named Morytania.}} Before he completely took over Hallowvale
[[Queen Efaritay]]
who was also a renowned botanist
bred all kinds of plant life to use against the vampyres

one of which was the [[blisterwood tree]] found in the heart of the city.{{CiteNPC|npc=Vanescula Drakan|loc=Sins of the Father|quote=Queen Efaritay was a renowned botanist. She used this to her advantage many times during the war

breeding all kinds of plant life to use against us. One of these plants was the Blisterwood tree. The icyene used the sap of this tree to create poisons that were deadly to vampyres.}} Unable to destroy the tree
the vampyres sealed it within Efaritay's old [[Arboretum (location)|Arboretum]]
with the Drakans ordering that no one is to enter the building.{{CiteNPC|npc=Desmodus Lasiurus|loc=Sins of the Father|quote=No one can go in the Arboretum
by order of the Drakan family themselves.}} During this time

the [[Archpriest of the Unicorn]] and his followers also began to create safeguards for the [[Hallowed Sepulchre]]{{CiteNPC|npc=Archpriest of the Unicorn|quote=The [Justiciar of the Unicorn] said he was going to confront these [vampyres] but that I should stay to protect the secrets within [the Hallowed Sepulchre]... I carried out my duties though. As we progressed further
we became more experienced at creating the traps. Each one was more deadly than the last. Eventually
when our work was done

I performed the last rites for each of my followers and sealed them within the coffins on the final floor.}} to prevent the vampyres from gaining access to the secrets and treasure within.{{CiteNPC|npc=Mysterious Stranger (Hallowed Sepulchre)|quote=Before they were driven out by the vampyres
the Saradominists used their magic to safeguard this place. The dead here were buried with the wealth they had in life. To protect these riches
the Saradominists enchanted the statues within the Sepulchre to create various defences.}}

Varlamore.name: Varlamore
npcs: Commander Fullore|quote=Zyanyi Arkan
the Sun Queen. She's the ruler of Varlamore
the kingdom in the south.}} To the distinction of other human kingdoms
who primarily worship [[Saradomin]]
the Varlamorians practice a religion officially named as [[Losanium]]
which involves the worship of the sun god [[Ralos]]
{{CiteNPC|npc=Brother Aimeri|quote=I am a travelling monk from the distant land of Varlamore... I worship Ralos
a common practice where I am from.}}{{CiteNPC|npc=Alina|loc=Children of the Sun|quote=The sun plays an important role in Varlamorian life. In fact
they worship it!}} and the moon god [[Ranul]]; however
most people focus their worship to one of the two. Varlamore is also littered with ruins of the [[Old Ones]]
{{CiteText|text=Kasonde's journal|quote=Find your way into the southern Kingdom of Varlamore

and you'll be presented with a huge range of interpretations. Not too surprising when you consider that the kingdom is littered with ruins from this ancient race.}} an ancient race that went extinct sometime during the beginning of the [[God Wars]].

Great Temple.name: Great Temple
npcs: High Priest (Sophanem)|loc=Contact!|quote=We Menaphites are believers in many gods. I
in my position as head priest of Icthlarin
still give praise to Tumeken and Elidinis each day at this very altar.}} The [[Contact!]] quest is started in the Great Temple
and it is visited frequently during [[Icthlarin's Little Helper]].

Abandoned Mine.name: Abandoned Mine
npcs: Zealot|loc=Haunted Mine|quote=Well
below the very ground you stand upon lies an intricate network on tunnels that make up the abandoned Mort Ridge mines.|name=Mort Ridge}}

Ruins of Tapoyauik.name: Ruins of Tapoyauik
npcs: Forebearer Fides|quote=This temple was built atop Tapoyauik
a ruined fortress of the Old Ones. They walked the world during the last cycle
and when the time came for their cycle to end
they embraced their destiny willingly.}} The [[Twilight Temple]] was later built on top of the ruins of the fortress
during the reign of [[Imafore Tullus|Emperor Imafore]].

Kourend Castle.name: Kourend Castle
npcs: Lord Trobin Arceuus|quote=I was there when Kharedst the Builder opened Kourend Castle}} While it is not explicitly stated whom in the line of Kharedst the title of 'the Builder' was attributed to
it is possible to make a reasonable inference with regard to his identity based on a letter addressed to [[Jonathan]] published in the [[Postbag from the Hedge]]. In his response
he mentions a census conducted by King Kharedst the Builder
containing "countless records of mothers without sons or husbands"

which in his estimation provides "fascinating insight into life before and after the War of the Five Houses".{{CitePostbag|issue=27|author=Jonathan|letter=4}} The conclusion that could be drawn from this document is that King Kharedst the Builder came to power immediately following the War of the Five Houses
meaning he would have been the first of his line
[[King Kharedst I]].

Menaphos.name: Menaphos
npcs: Osman|loc=Contact!|quote=Our two kingdoms were at war with one another for centuries. They tried to expand their kingdom northwards many times over the years
but we held them off. The desert is a great equalizer{{sic}}. It's very difficult to move large armies about in it
particularly if you don't have ready access to water.}} The two powers are at peace now
but hostilities still have not subsided and could easily flare up again.{{CiteNPC|npc=Scout (Shantay Pass)|loc=The General's Shadow|quote=The fighting in the desert has come to a stop. However
there is still much distrust between Menaphos and Al Kharid. It seems like it would be possible to reignite the war if needed.}} In fact

Spymaster [[Osman]] of Al Kharid has agents inside the city causing civil unrest and he claims he would be 'lynched on sight' should he set foot inside Menaphos or [[Sophanem]] and that the Menaphites would be very interested in extracting 'delicate information' from him and punishing him for his actions.{{CiteNPC|npc=Osman|loc=Contact!|quote=I've had my people instigate a bit of civil unrest. Officially our cities may be at peace
but I have some old scores to settle first.}} Despite the continuing hostilities
attempts have been made to improve relations

such as the construction of bridges over the [[River Elid]].{{CiteNews|author=Chris J|url=https://secure.runescape.com/m=news/desert-month-finale|title=Desert Month Finale|newsdate=26 April 2005|quote=A bridge across the River Elid has recently been constructed
yet another signal of the warming relations between the Kharidians and the Menaphites
opening up even more areas in our huge desert expansion.}}

Lassar Undercity.name: Lassar Undercity
npcs: Ketla|quote=When the barbarians came
many tried to fight. I should have fought with them
but I turned away. I had a duty to my people
but I abandoned them. The barbarians had blocked all exits
so the only way to flee was down. I hid down here while my people died
but now I pay the price for my choice.}}

Gielinor.name: Gielinor
npcs: Squire (Veteran)|quote=[Player: What's 'Gielinor'?] It is the name that Guthix gave to this world
so we honour him with its use.}} Gielinor's mainland comprises the [[Misthalin]]
[[Asgarnia]]
[[Kandarin]] and [[Morytania]] [[kingdom|kingdoms]]
the [[Kharidian Desert]]
the [[Wilderness]]
the south-western ogre lands of the [[Feldip Hills]]
the hidden elven lands of [[Tirannwn]]
and the northern [[Fremennik Province]] and [[Troll Country]].

Wizards' Tower.name: Wizards' Tower
npcs: Archmage Sedridor|loc=Rune Mysteries|quote=The rediscovery of runecrafting had such a large impact on the world
that it marked the dawn of the Fifth Age. It also resulted in the birth of our order
and the construction of the first Wizards' Tower.}} Initially
the Order was welcoming of all researching wizards
regardless of their religion or race
{{CiteNPC|npc=Archmage Sedridor|quote=For years

the tower was a hub of magical research. Wizards of all races and religions were welcomed into our order.}} though it has been claimed that Zamorakian wizards were barred from certain research topics.{{CiteNPC|npc=Archmage Sedridor|quote=They banned Zamorakian wizards from certain areas of study
claiming them to be too dangerous. In reality
they [Saradominists] just wanted that knowledge for themselves.}}

Twilight Temple.name: Twilight Temple
npcs: Prince Itzla Arkan|quote=The temple here was built not long before the War of Betrayal. It is said that Imafore wanted somewhere dedicated to Ranul that would rival the Teomat. [...] Anyway
the temple was considered an affront to both the Church of Ralos and the Sect of Ranul. After Imafore died
most people were more than happy to see it abandoned.}}

Crypt (White Knights' Castle).name: Crypt (White Knights' Castle)
npcs: Squire (Crypt)|quote=The greatest White Knights are buried here
after a lifetime in the service of Saradomin.}} is being cleaned (or rather: supposed to be cleaned) by the squire [[Vicks]]
and contains a portal to [[Death's Office]].

Shayzien Administration.name: Shayzien Administration
npcs: Commissioner Anwar|quote=This is the Shayzien Administration. The city of Shayzien is run from here.}} [[Commissioner Anwar]]
who is in charge of the Shayzien Constabulary

assists [[Lord Shiro Shayzien]] with the day to days of the city while he and focuses on the ongoing war with the [[lizardmen]] in the [[Shayzien Encampment]].{{CiteNPC|npc=Commissioner Anwar|quote=A lot of focus right now is on the war with the lizardmen. Most senior members of the [[Shayzien Army]]
including Lord Shayzien himself
are working out of the Shayzien Encampment instead.}}

Necropolis.name: Necropolis
npcs: Priest (Sophanem)}}

Dorgesh-Kaan.name: Dorgesh-Kaan
npcs: Mistag|loc=The Lost Tribe|quote=Our ancient legends say that goblins were created by an evil god in order to fight in a huge war. This god sent the Dorgeshuun tribe to fight a battle where all would die.}} However
the Dorgeshuun
at one point
became resistant to the idea of having to sacrifice their lives for their god and
after being sent off to do battle for him once more

they instead sneaked off into a hole where they could hide from his wrath.{{citeNPC|npc=Mistag|loc=The Lost Tribe|quote=But our ancestors escaped by hiding in a deep hole in the ground where our god could not find us. Eventually an earthquake sealed the hole and they were forever safe.}} After a cave-in
their refuge had been cut-off from the surface world until recent events involving the player. The city was founded around 2900 years ago during the [[Fourth Age]]
though the leadership began to shift from their generals to the council that advised them.{{citeNPC|npc=Goblin scribe|loc=Dorgesh-Kaan|quote=In the twenty-ninth century since the founding of the city

one of the miners broke through a wall into the cellar of a surface dwelling.}} A [[Dorgeshuun Civil War|civil war]] erupted and subsequently ended with the council-led republic of the Dorgeshuun victorious
the city continued developing to become one of the largest cities in ''[[RuneScape]]'' in the swamp-like [[Lumbridge]] underground
complete with its unique technologies and culture.{{citeNPC|npc=Goblin scribe|loc=Dorgesh-Kaan|quote=At first
Dorgesh-Kaan was ruled over by generals
just as the tribe had been when it was on the surface. Each general succeeded the last by defeating him in combat. The people voted to become a republic
but General Bonehelm refused to give up power
and so the Dorgeshuun Civil War began. The generals were advised by a council of elders
but the Dorgeshuun were no longer an army
and many of the people felt that the council should have authority.}}{{citeNPC|npc=Goblin scribe|loc=Dorgesh-Kaan|quote=There was a bloody battle
and General Bonehelm was driven back again into his base. But General Bonehelm's mining had weakened the stone around his base
and the retreating army's footsteps caused the roof to collapse
crushing his army. That was the last time one Dorgeshuun has raised arms against another.}} In the present day

the city is open to [[Lumbridge]] visitors after [[Mistag]] and the [[cave goblin miner]]s accidentally breached the walls of the [[Lumbridge Castle#Cellar|Lumbridge Castle cellar]] and a peace treaty was signed between Dorgesh-Kaan and Lumbridge.

Ah Za Rhoon.name: Ah Za Rhoon
npcs: Trufitus|quote=It is from an ancient language. The direct translation is... 'Magnificence floating on water'. (...) Even the great priest Zadimus who built the temple did not survive. Some say that Rashiliyia caused the temple to collapse.|loc=Shilo Village}} After being lost for many years
the temple became a legend
making many doubt its existence. This temple is visited during the [[Shilo Village]] quest.

Great Kourend.name: Great Kourend
npcs: Councillor Andrews|quote=The five houses of Kourend each have their own leader who rules over their city. The leaders of the individual houses must enforce and obey the laws set out by the Kourend Council
but can otherwise rule as they see fit.}} However
after the events of [[A Kingdom Divided]]
Great Kourend is once again ruled by a monarchy.

Phoenix Gang Hideout.name: Phoenix Gang Hideout
npcs: Baraek|loc=Shield of Arrav|quote=They're operating there under the name of the VTAM Corporation. Be careful. The Phoenixes ain't the types to be messed about.}}{{CiteNPC|npc=Straven|quote=Hey! You can't go in there. Only authorised personnel of the VTAM Corporation are allowed beyond this point.}} During the [[Shield of Arrav]] [[quest]]
the Phoenix Gang Hideout is accessible to members of the gang. Upon joining the gang
players are given a [[Weapon store key|key]] to the weapons store room
which is next door to the hideout. If the player kills the [[weaponsmaster]]

they can steal a [[Phoenix crossbow]]. This [[crossbow (weapon)|crossbow]] can only use [[bolts]] up to [[Bronze bolts|bronze]]. The store room also contains a spawn of [[grapes]] which [[Spawning|respawn]] every 43.5 seconds if taken.

Ruins of Camdozaal.name: Ruins of Camdozaal
npcs: Ramarno|quote=The Forge powers the entire city
or what's left of it at least.}}

Lassar.name: Lassar
npcs: Azzanadra |quote=Do the shining spires of Lassar still stand? |loc=Desert Treasure I}} It existed atop what is now known as [[Ice Mountain]]
a large mountain in northern [[Asgarnia]]. At the time
Asgarnia is believed to have been much colder than it is today
yielding snow year-round; yet nearly all of it had been settled by the Zarosians.

Zarosian Empire.name: Zarosian Empire
npcs: The Great Guardian|quote=Many sought to claim this artefact for themselves
including servants of the Fallen Empire.}}

Farming Guild.name: Farming Guild
npcs: Guildmaster Jane|quote=After the Shayzien Army cleared out the lizardmen in this area
I founded this guild with some fellow Hosidius farmers.}} Despite the risks of the lizardmen just across [[River Molch]]
the discoveries made here
along with the heat coming from [[Mount Karuulm]] just north-east
allows the guild to grow flora that would never survive in [[Great Kourend]]'s climate

{{CiteNPC|npc=Guildmaster Jane|quote=The heat of the volcano allows us to grow things here that would never survive in the climate of Kourend. The discoveries we have made here are worth the extra risk.}} such as the [[Hespori]] and the [[celastrus tree]].

The Scar.name: The Scar
npcs: The Great Guardian|loc=Temple of the Eye|quote=No part of the Abyss is more dangerous than the Scar.}} being described as the brain of an unfathomably large chthonian demon named {{RSL|Hostilius}}.{{CiteNews|url=https://secure.runescape.com/m=news/qa-summary-10022022?oldschool=1|title=Q&A Summary 10/02/2022|newsdate=15 February 2022|quote=The Abyss or at least a part of The Abyss the player visits in Old School are inside Hostilius' body. I think you probably get that vibe from the way it all looks.}}{{CiteGeneral|url=https://oldschool.runescape.wiki/w/Talk:Desert_Treasure_II_-_The_Fallen_Empire#Lore_Q&A_summary|title=Desert Treasure II Lore Q&A Livestream|author=[[Mod Ed]]|date=3 August 2023|quote=For the original area of the Abyss you go to
where you've got the portals to the runecrafting altars
we imagined that we're in the heart

or the stomach maybe. Then you've got the area where you fight the Sire; those are very clearly the lungs. Then this [the Scar] is now the brain.}} A rift leading to it is found within the [[Temple of the Eye (location)|Temple of the Eye]]

where abyssal creatures come through it; the rift is periodically closed as part of the [[Guardians of the Rift]] [[minigame]]. Partial completion of [[Desert Treasure II]] is required to access the Scar.

Hallowvale.name: Hallowvale
npcs: Vanescula Drakan|quote=Long ago
the land of Morytania was known as Hallowvale and it was ruled over by a race of Saradominists called the icyene.}} The kingdom was once a fertile
arable land with forests and farms
{{CiteText|text=Histories of the hallowland|quote=It is said that before the dark Lord Drakan arrived in Morytania
a very different land existed. A green land
pleasant and bounteous. Sufficient to please many hundreds of farmers
and to supply large towns
villages and cities with food.}} but fell to the [[Vampyres]] during the [[God Wars]]
after which it was renamed [[Morytania]].{{CiteNPC|npc=Vanescula Drakan|quote=Hallowvale was taken over by [the vampyres]
and Lowerniel became ruler of the newly named Morytania.}} The capital was the large city that is now known as [[Meiyerditch]].

Mac's island.name: Mac's island
npcs: Mac|quote=None of yer bis'ness.}}

Catacombs of Kourend.name: Catacombs of Kourend
npcs: Kharedst's memoirs|quote=The entrance below may be below the earth

but that realm lies beyond the reach of us mere mortals.}} while also being beneath the kingdom.{{CiteNPC|npc=Konar quo Maten|quote=The Catacombs of Kourend are located beneath Great Kourend.}} The Catacombs are also enchanted with powerful magic that prevents the monsters within from escaping;{{CiteText|text=Kharedst's memoirs|author=Rose|quote=I know of the powerful magic that keeps them bound below.}} conversely
it is supposedly difficult for "mere mortals" to enter the Catacombs as well
though players can enter the area without issues.

The Proudspire.name: The Proudspire
npcs: Curator Herminius|quote=Imafore soon found himself facing as much resistance from within as he did from Kourend. The end result was predictable. Imafore and his forces found themselves trapped between two armies at the Battle of the Proudspire. He was captured and executed
bringing an end to the Tullus dynasty.}}

River of Souls.name: River of Souls
npcs: The Sage (Shattered Relics League)|quote=Reality as you know it has many layers
all slightly different with their own rules. Through the power granted to me
I brought us to this layer using the River-Between. The River of Souls.|name=Sage}}

Isle of Souls.name: Isle of Souls
npcs: Ancient Ghost|quote=We [Armadyleans] were here to claim something. To protect it. But everything else is unclear.}} however it was claimed by [[Bandos]]

who evidently used it to destroy not only the Armadyleans{{CiteNPC|npc=Ancient Ghost|quote=Big High War God use the shiny to kill the chickens! Now we clear up the rest!}} but his own army as well.{{CiteNPC|npc=Player|quote=Sorry to be the bearer of bad news
but I think this 'shiny' might have killed you as well.}} This resulted in some of those slain becoming [[Ancient Ghost|ancient ghost]]s

unable to move on to the next world. The artefact may have been later used by [[Nomad]] to build the [[Soul Obelisk]].{{CiteNPC|npc=Zimberfizz|quote=I saw [Nomad] build [the Soul Obelisk] with me own eyes. I were the one who 'ad to carry his materials to this island!}}

River Varla.name: River Varla
npcs: Curator Herminius|quote=The name comes from the River Varla that separated Talkasti and Perican territory.}}

Abyssal Space.name: Abyssal Space
npcs: Mage of Zamorak|quote=It is a hard place to describe. We often refer to it as another plane
but that isn't quite accurate. If anything
it is more like a plane that sits between all other planes.}} Its relationship to other planes is described as that of a {{WP|tesseract}} or hypercube

{{CiteText|text=Abyssal book|quote=...the Abyss is somewhat of a tesseract or hypercube with a direct relation to our dimension.}} and is mostly known for being the primary medium for teleportation magic and inter-planar travel.{{CiteNPC|npc=Mage of Zamorak|quote=It [the Abyss] can be used as an effective hub for teleportation. In fact
all teleportation that we know of uses the Abyss
you just don't realise it.}}{{CiteNPC|npc=Mage of Zamorak|quote=Whenever you use a teleport spell
that spell is actually travelling through the Abyss and using it to link two places together.}}

Temple of the Lesser Gods.name: Temple of the Lesser Gods
npcs: Jex|loc=Contact!|quote=I know bits and pieces about its history. I help maintain this place and even held services until recently. Please excuse its current sorry state. Some strange scarab creatures burst up from the cellars a few months ago. We fought them back into some kind of dungeon but
in doing so
the temple and the bank beneath were devastated.}} Following the death of several Sophanites who entered the dungeon

the tunnels were shut off by a trapdoor with a complicated lock and two [[Sophanem guard]]s were stationed in the remains of the bank.{{CiteNPC|npc=Jex|loc=Contact!|quote=It's incredibly dangerous down there. We've lost far too many townsfolk already who underestimated the dangers. There are some fearsome traps and vicious monsters lurking in the darkness. [...] We've posted a number of guards there to hold back the scarab monsters. There is a barricaded trapdoor there that is a little complicated to open.}}  There is a ladder leading to the roof in the corner of the temple
but there is nothing there.

Lady Zay.name: Lady Zay
npcs: Captain Bentley|loc=Lunar Diplomacy|quote=It was a steal from the Karamjan shipyards. And when I say it was a steal

I mean to say that myself and some of the lads broke in and stole it one night.}} He mentions that they had to remodel the ship's interior because it was built for a crew that was small in stature.{{CiteNPC|npc=Captain Bentley|loc=Lunar Diplomacy|quote=I don't know who they were building these warships for
but whoever it was seemed to be a little on the short side. We had to do a little remodelling of the doors and rooms so that we didn't have to crouch around everywhere
but I've finally got her just how I want her
and we have enough cannons down below decks to bombard a small town I'd wager!}} This is a direct reference to the events of [[Monkey Madness I]]
during which [[Glough]] secretly raises an army of ships for gnomekind to take over Gielinor.
